          <msContents>
            <summary>
              <p>Single parchment folio, Shelfmark: Mark Mersiowsky: Sig.isl. 18 ; Qurʾānic Text: Q 8:72-9:11; Lines per page: 17; Script style: kūfī B.Ib; Dimensions: 210 x 130 mm; Estimated date of production: 1000-1200.</p>
              <p> </p>
              <p>This codex fragment belongs to the collection of Mark Mersiowsky (Stuttgart), who gave to permission to take samples for radiocarbon analysis (financed by the project Coranica, generously funded by ANR (Paris) and the German DFG. The obtained measurement, 1233,21 BP corresponds to four intervals: 689-696, 701-742, 772-779, and 784-879 (according to the callibration of Oxcal 2020; 95,4% σ2). The calibrated result streches in four intervals the time span between 689 to 879, because of the peak and the plateau of the calibration curve. Taking into account the script style (an ancient script style of which documents for example Tübingen <ref target="https://corpuscoranicum.de/en/manuscripts/107/page/1r">Ma VI 165</ref> belong to the 7th century) and the horizontal format, a date estimate between 690 and 750 could be suggested. However, a date between 772 and 879 cannot be excluded but seems less probable.    </p>
            </summary>
